                    "company": "INSERM",
                    "description": "Principal investigation: Epigenetic study of meloe gene, encoding for melanoma associated antigens. \nWe previously characterized two melanoma antigens MELOE-1 and MELOE-2 derived from a polycistronic RNA overexpressed in the melanocytic lineage. This transcription profile was due to hypomethylation of meloe proximal promoter in melanomas and melanocytes. In this study we investigated whether this demethylation was restricted to meloe promoter or was linked to a general lack of methylation at meloe locus in the melanocytic lineage. We established the methylation pattern of the locus spanning more than 40kb, focusing on CpG islands, using DNA bi-sulfite conversion and pyrosequencing. We found that demethylation process specifically observed in the melanocytic lineage, concerns a large promoter area and not the whole meloe locus. This allows updating a tight regulation of meloe transcription in this lineage, suggesting tissue-specific epigenetic mechanisms.",
